    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Solve the following equation algebraically.</p>
<p>{@quad1@}=0, \(x=\)[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]][[feedback:prt1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Note that we can write the given equation as a quadratic in \({@aa@}^x\). Therefore we can factorise it to obtain
\[
{@quad2@} = 0.
\]
Note that \({@aa@}^xx = -{@cc@}\) cannot happen since this is negative. Therefore we have that 
\[
{@aa@}^x = {@aa@}^{@bb@},
\]
thus since the base numbers are the same we can equate the indices to get that the only solution is \(x = {@ta1@}\).
</p>]]></text>
